modules.description: Provides functions to wrap exceptions with a trace of source code locations and to extract or combine these traces when exceptions are re-raised. Works with custom exception types and maintains a list of file and line numbers as the exception propagates. Used to accurately track the origin and path of exceptions in complex or asynchronous code flows.

Adds location information to exceptions and manages exception traces, allowing for detailed error tracking. It works with exceptions and location data, enabling stack traces to be captured and formatted. Use cases include debugging by preserving and displaying exception origins, and re-raising exceptions with updated trace information.
